values:
Shivers ran down my spine
As you brushed your fingers
Across my lips.

Your eyes captured mine,
And I forgot to exhale.
I wondered if you would still do this
If you knew how badly I needed you.

I wish I could hot-wire you
Between my ribs;
Create a steady circuit
Instead of the usual irregular beat
That flat-lines whenever you're near.

You kiss is sedating, and hallucinating,
and infuriating, and intoxicating
All at the same time.
{the perfect drug}

&& Boy, am I addicted to you
In the worst way.
